commText: Abhishek Sharma and Head are at the crease. Abhishek Sharma is on strike. Will Jacks will open the attack
Will Jacks to Abhishek Sharma, no run, tossed up delivery around off, a lot slower through the air, Abhishek Sharma shoulders arms
Will Jacks to Abhishek Sharma, no run, flat and quick on off, Abhishek Sharma defends it towards cover with soft hands
Will Jacks to Abhishek Sharma, 2 runs, fraction short on off, Abhishek Sharma shimmies down the track and punches it to wide long-off for a couple of runs
Will Jacks to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, width on offer and Abhishek Sharma thumps this over the infield at cover. That's the first boundary of the match
Will Jacks to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, touch short on middle and leg, Abhishek Sharma works it through the leg-side for a single
Will Jacks to Head, no run, full and straight on middle and leg, Head defends it back to the bowler
Topley has a slip in place for Abhishek
Reece Topley, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Topley to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, back of a length around off, Abhishek Sharma knocks it into the off-side
Topley to Head, FOUR, Head opens his account with a four! Drifting on the pads and Head has flicked this away to the deep mid-wicket fence. One bounce and over the boundary
Topley to Head, SIX, even better. Topley goes full off, the ball shapes away a touch as Head launches it straight as an arrow, that's half-a-dozen more
Topley to Head, 2 runs, miscued but safe. Was a shorter delivery on off and Head goes for a pull, gets a top edge over mid-wicket and takes a couple of runs
Topley to Head, 1 run, 133.3kph, short of a length outside off, shaping away from the batter, Head steers it to square third man for a single
Topley to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, an expensive over by Topley, 20 runs from it. This was short on leg and Abhishek Sharma flicks it over fine leg for his first maximum. SRH off to a flying start
Jacks to continue..
Will Jacks to Head, 1 run, tad short on off, Head punches it to long-off for a single
Will Jacks to Abhishek Sharma, no run, on the shorter side again as Abhishek Sharma punches it to the fielder at cover off his back foot
Will Jacks to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, 94kph, pushed through on a length, Abhishek Sharma drives it along the carpet to long-off
Will Jacks to Head, no run, full and quick on leg, Head goes for a slogsweep, gets hit on the pads thigh though
Will Jacks to Head, 1 run, clever bowling. Goes short and quick as the batter advances down the wicket, Head gently nudges it towards mid-wicket for one
Will Jacks to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, full and straight on off, Abhishek Sharma dances down the track and drives it to long-off for a single
Topley taken out of the attack after an expensive first over..
Yash Dayal, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Yash Dayal to Abhishek Sharma, wide, short and wide outside off, Sharma gets beaten on the cut, called a wide by the umpire. That moved away slightly, hence missed the tramline
Yash Dayal to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, too much width on offer, Abhishek Sharma frees his arms and carves it over backward point for four more. He's dealing in boundaries

Yash Dayal to Abhishek Sharma, no run, appeal for a caught behind turned down! On a length outside off, shaping away from the batter, Abhishek Sharma has a poke and connects thin air. Was very close to the outside edge
Yash Dayal to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, on a length around off, Abhishek Sharma taps it in front of point with soft hands, scampers across to the other end
Yash Dayal to Head, no run, 126.7kph, short and wide outside off, Head slashes at it, gets beaten
Yash Dayal to Head, no run, this one swings back in from over the wicket, Head goes for a cut, almost nicks it behind
Yash Dayal to Head, 1 run, 132.7kph, short of a length outside off, Head times his cut through backward point, just a single
Here comes Ferguson. His first ball for RCB..
Lockie Ferguson, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Ferguson to Head, no run, starts off with a short ball outside off, Head tries to guide it towards third man, but gets beaten due to the pace and bounce
Ferguson to Head, SIX, 147.7kph, fired on the pads and it sails over the fence. Flicks it over deep backward square leg for half-a-dozen with nonchalance
Ferguson to Head, SIX, 50-run stand up! On the shorter side, Head stays put and pulls it over deep mid-wicket for back-to-back sixes
Ferguson to Head, 1 run, back of a length around off, punched to cover where a misfield results in a single
Ferguson to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, short of a length outside off, Abhishek Sharma plays this late, steering it to third man for a single
Ferguson to Head, FOUR, 18 runs from the over! Short of a length around off, Head stays put and slams it right over the bowler's head, that almost goes the distance. Not a pleasant start for Ferguson
Yash Dayal to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, width on offer, Abhishek Sharma slices it over point and the ball lands just in front of Lomror who was charging in from the deep
Yash Dayal to Head, SIX, stand and deliver! Yash Dayal goes short and Head stands tall and nails the pull over long-on, clean as a whistle
Yash Dayal to Head, 2 runs, slower delivery at 108.5kph, Head goes down on his knee and flat-bats this over the bowler's head, du Plessis from mid-off sprints back and stops it with a slide
Yash Dayal to Head, SIX, into the stands again! A short ball by Yash Dayal and Head has smashed it over deep mid-wicket for a flat six. Showing no mercy is Head..

Yash Dayal to Head, FOUR, fifty for Head! Gets there in 20 balls. A short and wide ball outside off, Head smashes it towards cover where the fielder gets his hands to it, fails to stop the ball and it's away to the fence in no time
Yash Dayal to Head, 1 run, full and quick outside off, Head drives it to cover where the fielder stops it with a dive to his left
Over Summary (1-6): -- Jacks starts on a tight note. -- Topley goes for 20 in his first over -- 50 up inside the 4th over as Ferguson goes for 18 -- Head brings up his fifty and SRH score 76 in PP

Strategic timeout! SRH off to a fantastic start. Head has notched up his fifty within the powerplay. The pacers have gone the distance, will RCB be able to bounce back after break? ICYMI: Jacks conceded 11 runs in 2 overs. Rest - 65 runs in 4 overs..
Will Jacks [2.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Will Jacks to Head, 2 wides, fired down the leg-side as it results in a two wides
Will Jacks to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, tad short on middle and leg, Abhishek Sharma pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single

Will Jacks to Head, FOUR, no stopping Head! The break makes no difference. This was on the shorter side and Head rocks back to cut it past the fielder at backward point. Was in the air for a bit, but the batter is safe
Will Jacks to Head, SIX, smoked into the stands. A tossed up delivery on middle and leg, Head goes down on his knee and slogsweeps it over deep mid-wicket for half-a-dozen
Will Jacks to Head, SIX, carnage! A short ball by Will Jacks, Head rocks back and pummels it over deep mid-wicket for six more. He has raced away to 68* in no time..
Will Jacks to Head, 1 run, short and wide outside off, cut through the off-side by Head for a single
Will Jacks to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, a lot slower through the air, on the shorter side as Abhishek Sharma nudges it to mid-on for one

Highest Powerplay scores for SRH (IPL): 81/1 vs MI Hyderabad 2024 79/0 vs KKR Hyderabad 2017 78/1 vs CSK Hyderabad 2024 77/0 vs PK Hyderabad 2019 77/0 vs DC Dubai 2020 76/0 vs RCB Bengaluru 2024 Three of the top six scores have come in 2024 season alone.
Vijaykumar Vyshak, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, 100 up for SRH! Pitched up by the bowler on off, Abhishek Sharma stands tall and launches this over the bowler's head for a towering six
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, back of a length around off, Abhishek Sharma slices it towards the off-side for a single
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Head, 1 run, full and wide outside off, Head drills it to long-off for a single
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, banged in short by Vijaykumar Vyshak, Abhishek Sharma pulls it to deep mid-wicket on the bounce
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Head, 1 run, on the shorter side, Head smashes it straight past the bowler for a single
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, banged in short by Vijaykumar Vyshak, Abhishek Sharma pulls it to long-on for a single
RCB pace attack in Powerplay in IPL 2024: 3 wkts Avg 125.67 SR 72.0 ER 10.47 They are at the bottom of the table in each of these parameters.
Reece Topley [1.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack
Topley to Abhishek Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Topley to Abhishek Sharma, out Caught by Ferguson!! Topley gets the breakthrough! Their two overseas pacers in action on this occasion. Was back of a length and Abhishek Sharma flicked it to deep backward square leg. Lockie settles under the skier and completes a safe catch. Abhishek Sharma walks back after playing a cameo, however, the danger man - Head is still out in the middle. Abhishek Sharma c Ferguson b Topley 34(22) [4s-2 6s-2]
Heinrich Klaasen, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Topley to Klaasen, no run, back of a length around off, Klaasen defends it back to the bowler
Topley to Klaasen, wide, short and wide outside off, Klaasen goes for a flashy cut, gets beaten, in fact this was out of his reach
Topley to Klaasen, 1 run, short of a length around off, Klaasen steers it to third man for a single
Topley to Head, wide, banged in short by Topley, a slower one that sails over the batter's head who was trying to upper cut it

Topley to Head, FOUR, edged away to the boundary! On a length around middle, Head moves a little leg side and tries to push it away, gets an outside edge past short third man and that's four more for the southpaw
Scoring 50+ in Powerplay for SRH (IPL) \n6 X David Warner \n2 X Travis Head
Topley to Head, no run, yorker length delivery by Topley and this has been squeezed back to the bowler

Topley to Head, FOUR, cut away! Topley goes short, Head rocks back in the crease and cuts it over backward point, just manages to elude the fielder inside the circle. Started the over with a wicket, however, ends up conceding 11 runs does Head
STAT: 100+ partnership in just 43 balls - the joint fastest for SRH in IPL alongside Warner-Henriques for the second wicket vs RCB in Hyderabad in 2015
Lockie Ferguson [1.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack
Ferguson to Klaasen, 1 run, on a length around off, Klaasen drives it to wide mid-off where the fielder slides and gets his hands to it, just a single
Ferguson to Head, SIX, short and punished! Waits for it to arrive, gets in position and pulls it over deep backward square leg for a ferocious six. This is absolute carnage
Ferguson to Head, no run, yorker length ball and Head digs it back to the bowler
Ferguson to Head, 1 run, pitched up by the bowler on middle and leg, lofted to long-on for one
Ferguson to Klaasen, no run, short of a length around off, Klaasen looks to defend, gets beaten on the outside edge
Ferguson to Klaasen, 1 run, short and quick on off, Klaasen goes for a pull, gets an inside edge on to the thigh pad, a single taken
Yash Dayal [2.0-0-27-0] is back into the attack
Yash Dayal to Klaasen, 2 runs, on a length around leg, Klaasen flicks it to deep backward square leg where the fielder puts in a slide to stop it, saves a couple of runs
Yash Dayal to Klaasen, SIX, Klaasen joins the act! A slower delivery by Yash Dayal, tad short and Klaasen has smoked it over deep square leg for half-a-dozen. His first biggie of the night
Yash Dayal to Klaasen, 2 runs, back of a length on leg, Klaasen tucks it through backward square leg, calls for two and manages to get back in comfortably
Yash Dayal to Klaasen, 1 run, on a length outside off, Klaasen punches it through the off-side for a single
Yash Dayal to Head, wide, misses the tramline outside off, in fact, just on the line and it's called a wide
Yash Dayal to Head, no run, full and quick outside off, driven to cover by Head
Yash Dayal to Head, wide, attempts a slower one outside off, but it's too wide
Yash Dayal to Head, 1 run, yorker length ball to end the over, Head digs it towards the on-side for a single. A comparatively economical over by Yash Dayal
Over Summary (6-11): -- Jacks goes for 21 in his 3rd over -- Vyshak is welcomed into the attack with a sixer -- Topley gets rid of Sharma who departs for 34 -- Klaasen promoted in the batting order
Vijaykumar Vyshak [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Head, FOUR, on a length outside off, Head goes down on his knee and bludgeons it towards wide long-off. Moves into the 90s with that cracking boundary
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Head, FOUR, 150 up in the 12th over! On the shorter side, Head goes for a pull and gets a top edge over backward square leg. Races away once again
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Head, 2 runs, low full toss outside off, Head goes for a drive as the keeper gets his gloves to it, DK gets his glove to it, can't gather it though, they take a brace instead

Vijaykumar Vyshak to Head, FOUR, century for Head! Gets there in 39 balls. Removes his helmet and balances it on the handle of his bat to celebrate. What a fantastic knock this has been. Has to the most destructive innings of the season. This was pitched up by Vijaykumar Vyshak and Head smashed the leather out of it. Beats wide long-on and adds four more to the tally
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Head, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Head steers it to square third man for a single
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Klaasen, 1 run, 50-run stand up! Once again Head has done majority of the scoring in this partnership. Was a short ball as Klaasen slaps it to long-on for a single
Lockie Ferguson [2.0-0-27-0] is back into the attack

Ferguson to Klaasen, SIX, running out of words, just like RCB have run out of ideas. This was right into the slot, an overpitched delivery and swings it over deep mid-wicket for the cleanest sixes of the night
Ferguson to Klaasen, leg byes, 1 run, back of a length on middle and leg, Klaasen gets an inside edge on to the thigh pad, takes a single
Ferguson to Head, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Ferguson to Head, out Caught by du Plessis!! Slower delivery does the trick. Head walks back after playing a fantastic knock. Gets a standing ovation from the SRH owners. Was a knuckle ball by Ferguson, tad fuller and Head tried to go hard again. Miscues it completely and du Plessis at mid-off takes a safe reverse cup to draw curtains to Head's stellar innings. Head c du Plessis b Ferguson 102(41) [4s-9 6s-8]

Fastest 100s in IPL by balls faced 30 C Gayle vs PWI Bengaluru 2013 37 Y Pathan vs MI Mumbai BS 2010 38 D Miller vs RCB Mohali 2013 39 T Head vs RCB Bengaluru 2024 42 A Gilchrist vs MI Mumbai DYP 2008
Aiden Markram, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Ferguson to Markram, 1 run, tad short on off, Markram steers it to third man for a single and opens his account
Ferguson to Klaasen, FOUR, banged in short and quick on leg, Klaasen goes for a pull, gets a top edge that flies over the keeper down the leg-side, four more to the tally
Ferguson to Klaasen, leg byes, 1 run, short of a length on middle and leg, Klaasen gets hit on the thigh pad as he ends up taking a leg bye
Mahipal Lomror, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Lomror to Klaasen, 1 run, shortish and outside off stump, Klaasen slaps it to deep cover
Lomror must be a brave man to bowl to Klaasen
Lomror to Markram, 1 run, Markram wants to watch the entertainment from the best seat - non striker end - so he guides to deep point and gets Klaasen back on strike
Lomror to Klaasen, wide, Lomror tries to hide it wide of off, too wide
Lomror to Klaasen, SIX, No. 1 of the over! Full and in the slot, oh that's easy peasy for me says Klaasen and muscles the lofted on-drive over long-on
Lomror to Klaasen, wide, Lomror fires way outside off stump again!

Lomror to Klaasen, wide, and again! Got to feel for the poor fellow. Had to bowl because of a strategical error they made by not using up one more Will Jacks over against LHBs. Now they can't bring him on to two right-handers and Lomror has to complete the fifth bowler's quota

Lomror to Klaasen, SIX, No. 2 of the over! This time, straighter, higher over long-on. Lomror tried to keep it out of Klaasens arc, didn't happen so he tries to hit the blockhole, instead Klaasen hits the ball miles over the boundary
Lomror to Klaasen, no run, back over the wicket and he fires this full on the pads, Klaasen misses the sweep and gets hit on the pad. Gold of a dot ball being a spinner against Klaasen

Lomror to Klaasen, 1 run, well done! It's a wide yorker that Klaasen had to reach out to and drill it past extra-cover. 18 off that over but you'd have to say pretty decent knowing how Klaasen murders spin for 25+ easily in an over
Vijaykumar Vyshak [2.0-0-27-0] is back into the attack
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Klaasen, no run, brilliant wide slower full delivery outside off stump, Klaasen swings and misses. Was beaten by change of pace

Vijaykumar Vyshak to Klaasen, FOUR, it's a mishit but it's a four! Got to feel for the bowler. Short and slow outside off stump, Klaasen dragged the pull off the under edge, ball escapes through square leg and splits the fielders in the deep
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Klaasen, 1 run, wide yorker, dug out to the off-side

Vijaykumar Vyshak to Markram, FOUR, in the airrrr and just over the man at cover! Faf at mid-off thought his mate had it covered and jumped in hope but it escapes overhead. Length delivery, Markram hit that on the rise and got away despite not exactly powering it well
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Markram, 1 run, worked away to deep mid-wicket

Vijaykumar Vyshak to Klaasen, SIX, full toss and Heinrich Klaasen completes his fifty off 23 balls and also brings up the team 200. Klaasen hardly tried to hit that hard, just put bat on ball and gave direction. The Orange Army is waving the flags in joy with the carnage their batters have put on
277 is in real danger
Reece Topley [2.0-0-31-1] is back into the attack
Topley to Markram, 1 run, slower delivery on the off stump, Markram works it to long-on

Topley to Klaasen, SIX, you miss the yorker just by an inch and still this guy can get under the ball and muscle it over long-on. DK looks in disbelief from behind. Topley missed the mark and Klaasen took it from his arc
Topley to Klaasen, 2 runs, very similar length, line slightly towards off stump so Klaasen goes straight down the ground and Faf had to really roll across to the right from long-off to cut it off
Topley to Klaasen, 1 run, low full toss, Klaasen flicks to deep mid-wicket
Topley to Markram, 1 run, good yorker angling in from round the wicket, Markram flicks this leg-side ball to long leg

Topley to Klaasen, 1 run, good placement there! Had their deep cover to the right than usual, otherwise this cover drive would have been a four. Full and in the slot, nailed that shot, got only one. Very good over in the context of this game. Only one boundary and 12 off it

Over Summary (12-16): -- Head slams a ton off 39 balls. -- Head falls for 102. Ferguson has his wicket -- Fifty off 23 balls for Klaasen as he tears into Lomror and Vyshak -- Klaasen and Markram add fifty off 19 balls

Timeout. 217. SRH clearly looking to bat RCB out of the game. 260 looks bare minimum they will get with batting left. If these to play out the over we could have our highest IPL score. RCB somehow need to keep this under 250. Whatever it is from here, it will be a mountain for them
Lockie Ferguson [3.0-0-38-1] is back into the attack
Ferguson to Klaasen, no run, lovely low full toss that Klaasen can't get under, dug out towards cover
RCB bowling coach during the timeout had an animated chat with his bowlers

Ferguson to Klaasen, SIX, that's on the roof! Sure the coach didn't tell to run in and bowl length. Klaasen murders that for a 106m hit and it's gone out of the ground! Just a simple lofted straight drive and he didn't even try to muscle that hard. That's how ridiculously this guy makes six hitting look easy
Fastest to 200 by a team in IPL 14.1 RCB vs PBKS Bengaluru 2016 (15 over match) 14.4 SRH vs MI Hyderabad 2024 14.6 SRH vs RCB Bengaluru 2024 15.2 KKR vs DC Vizag 2024
Ferguson to Klaasen, 1 run, dug out to deep mid-wicket
Ferguson to Markram, SIX, slot again, slot again and six over long-on again. The slower delivery this yes, good idea sure but dished out at length! Markram waits and happily launches it over long-on
Ferguson to Markram, 1 run, drags the slog to deep mid-wicket
Ferguson to Klaasen, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Ferguson to Klaasen, out Caught by Vijaykumar Vyshak!! That's one of the luckiest wickets you will get in cricket. Klaasen can't believe what he's seen. It's a high full toss outside off stump with no deep fielder behind square. So Klaasen thought he could just slice it for another boundary but had to reach out and toe-ended it to the right of backward point where Vyshak did the rest. This will surely make a difference of at least 15 runs to the final total. Ferguson celebrates his second wicket but what a brilliant display of hitting it was from Klaasen. Klaasen c Vijaykumar Vyshak b Ferguson 67(31) [4s-2 6s-7]
Abdul Samad, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Yash Dayal [3.0-0-41-0] is back into the attack

Yash Dayal to Markram, 2 runs, full and outside off stump, Markram crashes the drive to deep extra-cover. Lovely slide from Patidar to flick it back and he actually managed to do the flick again to ensure the ball didn't escape for four
233 - Highest team total vs RCB in all T20s surpassing 232/2 by PBKS in Dharamsla in 2011

Yash Dayal to Markram, no ball, in the airrr, taken! RCB have found a new way of getting wickets in cricket - bowl freebie full tosses outside off and have the batters caught behind square on the off-side! Oh hang on, the buzzer is off! Oh dear, Yash Dayal has overstepped and the joy is killed. Markram tried to reach out and slice, sliced it to the left of short third man and Topley did take a good low catch. All in vain though
Yash Dayal to Markram, no run, yorker outside off stump, Markram drills it to hand
Yash Dayal to Markram, 1 run, only a single down to long-on as he can't get the placement right
Yash Dayal to Abdul Samad, 1 run, back of the hand slower delivery, Samad mistimes to cover
Yash Dayal to Markram, 1 run, oh he misses out on a high full toss, drags it to deep mid-wicket

Yash Dayal to Abdul Samad, FOUR, spoils a very good over! Nice wide yorker, can't blame the bowler there, but full credit to Samad for squeeze it out past point, got the placement precise to beat the full length slide from the sweeper
37 more for the record total. RCB might have done well here to ensure that's happening today. Impact sub on for RCB, Yash Dayal out, Anuj Rawat in
Reece Topley [3.0-0-43-1] is back into the attack
Topley to Markram, 1 run, Markram tries to hit a maximum but he's not getting under the ball like Klaasen. Klaasen was hitting sixes off the same length. Markram only mistimes to the right of long-on
Topley to Abdul Samad, FOUR, slower delivery into the wicket, Samad hangs back and slaps the pull wide over mid-wicket for four
Topley to Abdul Samad, FOUR, oh look at that bat speed! Length and pace off from Topley, Samad this time muscles the drive past cover and he's placed it brilliantly to get four more

Topley to Abdul Samad, SIX, in the airrrr and smacks the roof! Maybe 277 isn't safe yet. Topley misses the yorker again, Samad gets under it and shows his prowess. Another muscular hit straight down the ground

Topley to Abdul Samad, SIX, full toss, you got to be kidding me! DK can do nothing but just look at the ball go all the way. Virat follows the trajectory from long-off! Poor ball from Topley, sure was the attempted yorker that went wrong. Samad accepts the gift and smacks it over long-off, a bit flatter this time

19* sixes in SRH innings \nMost sixes in an IPL match for SRH (Previous: 17 vs MI Hyderabad 2024) \nMost sixes in an IPL match vs RCB (Previous: 17 each by CSK thrice - Bengaluru 2018, Mumbai DYP 2022 & Bengaluru 2023)

Topley to Abdul Samad, FOUR, outside edgeee and it flies over the short third man fielder. They have already reached 266. Slower delivery outside off stump, Samad swings across the line and gets away with the edge. 25 off that Topley over
Vijaykumar Vyshak [3.0-0-43-0] is back into the attack
RCB review a wide. Given wide for height, come on, that's well above head height
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Markram, wide, just waste of time with that review. Slow short delivery, Markram lets it go knowing it's too high
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Markram, FOUR, tries the leg stump yorker but bowls slightly down leg and Markram tickles it past the keeper and to the right of short fine leg. 271 now

Vijaykumar Vyshak to Markram, SIX, 277 - they have equalled their own feat! Vijaykumar Vyshak tries the short slower delivery into the wicket, Markram waits on the back foot and smacks the pull over mid-wicket

Vijaykumar Vyshak to Markram, 1 run, there's the highest total in IPL ever and the SRH team and fans are celebrating already like a victory. Sure is a moment to enjoy such a great feat. Slower delivery outside off stump, Markram toe-ends the drive to long-off
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Abdul Samad, no run, beaten! Slower delivery outside off stump, Samad slogs and misses. Disappointed with himself

Vijaykumar Vyshak to Abdul Samad, SIX, in the airrrr and tipped over the bar! Very difficult chance for the man at deep mid-wicket. Great effort jumping high and get his right hand on it. Was a short of a length delivery at pace, Samad hits a flat pull and gets SIX

Most expensive figures in IPL 0/70 Basil Thampi vs RCB Bengaluru 2018 0/69 Yash Dayal vs KKR Ahmedabad 2023 1/68 Reece Topley vs SRH Bengaluru 2024 Previous most conceded by an overseas bowler was 66 each by Mujeeb Zadran against SRH in Hyderabad in 2019 and Kwena Maphaka vs SRH in Hyderabad in 2024.
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Abdul Samad, wide, well outside off stump, review again from RCB, third says it's still a wide so we have one more ball for this carnage to end

Vijaykumar Vyshak to Abdul Samad, 2 runs, in the airrrr, dropped a dolly. Slower delivery, Samad toe-ended the slog high. Deep mid-wicket ran in and got there, easy catch but he carried too much speed and spilled the catch

21:14 Local Time, 15:44 GMT, 21:14 IST: Phew, these guys, SRH! 277 the other day, they better it by 10 more today. Some of the brutal hitting you will see in cricket. But you also got to be honest and admit the bowling and strategies weren't great. Travis Head and Abhishek Sharma were given the role of being ultra aggressive in the powerplay and they executed to the T. They scared their opponents as early as the first six overs. Didn't matter who bowled after that start. Abhishek fell early but SRH wanted nothing but a kill today. In walked Klaasen at 3. The agony continued for the hosts. We had balls going deep into the stands, on the roof and even out of the ground. Head got his hundred off 39 balls, Klaasen got his fifty off 23 balls. Markram managed to keep the rate going, but with Klaasen going 277 looked safe. However, Samad put on a mega show in the 19th over to smack Topley for 4 4 6 6 4 and they eventually got the highest IPL total ever.

Travis Head: Nice wicket. Got to contribute at the right time. Just tried to maximise my opportunities. We got off to a really nice start. I don't know, that was proper batting. We have tried to take on the game (after quick starts). We just try to maximise the powerplay and then we try to keep going. Pat (Cummins) and Dan (Vettori) put pressure on the batting line up to make sure we keep going. All the guys are stepping up in each game.

Pitch sure is good for batting but it isn't as good as 287. Slower balls into the wicket were working and SRH will look to use that to their advantage like they did against MI when they made 277. RCB actually began well today with Jacks bowling 2 overs for only 11 runs. But for some reason - sure they would have wanted variety in the attack - they took Jacks off when he was keep it tight and to think it happened right after a Yash Dayal over where Head was put under a bit of pressure with a few dots was hard to understand. SRH's only other LHB was Shahbaz and wonder how saving up Jacks's over were going to help. They missed a potential chance of further troubling an edgy Head by removing Jacks. SRH would have also seen RCB field only four frontline bowlers and tried to take advantage. Anyway, the chase now!
